## Data Isolation

**Strategy**: {{patterns.isolation.strategy}}
**Isolation field**: `{{patterns.isolation.field}}`

- Every database query MUST filter by `{{patterns.isolation.field}}`
- API endpoints must derive the isolation value from the authenticated user's token — never from request parameters
- Verify isolation in both read and write operations
- {{patterns.isolation.description}}

### Isolation Checklist

- [ ] All queries filter by `{{patterns.isolation.field}}`
- [ ] Isolation field derived from auth token, not request body/params
- [ ] Cross-tenant access tested and blocked
- [ ] Bulk operations respect isolation boundaries
{{/if}}

---

## Compliance Checklist (All Code)

- [ ] No sensitive data in logs, error messages, or API responses
{{#if patterns.isolation.enabled}}
- [ ] Data isolation maintained in all queries
{{/if}}
- [ ] Audit trail for all sensitive data mutations
- [ ] Frontend meets WCAG 2.2 AA accessibility standards
- [ ] No hardcoded secrets or credentials
- [ ] Input validation on all user-supplied data
- [ ] Authorization checks on all protected operations

